## Overview
Implement the 4-phase collision detection algorithm for JSONL import. This determines how incoming issues match existing issues, handling ID conflicts, content deduplication, and external reference matching.

## Algorithm Phases

### Phase 1: External Reference Match
```rust
/// Check if incoming issue matches by external_ref (e.g., JIRA-123)
fn phase1_external_ref_match(
    incoming: &Issue,
    storage: &SqliteStorage,
) -> Option<CollisionMatch> {
    let external_ref = incoming.external_ref.as_ref()?;

    // Query for existing issue with same external_ref
    let existing = storage.find_by_external_ref(external_ref)?;

    Some(CollisionMatch {
        phase: 1,
        existing_id: existing.id.clone(),
        match_type: MatchType::ExternalRef,
        confidence: 1.0,  // Exact match
    })
}
```

### Phase 2: Content Hash Match
```rust
/// Check if incoming issue matches by content_hash (deduplication)
fn phase2_content_hash_match(
    incoming: &Issue,
    storage: &SqliteStorage,
) -> Option<CollisionMatch> {
    // Compute content hash of incoming issue
    let content_hash = compute_content_hash(incoming);

    // Query for existing issue with same content hash
    let existing = storage.find_by_content_hash(&content_hash)?;

    Some(CollisionMatch {
        phase: 2,
        existing_id: existing.id.clone(),
        match_type: MatchType::ContentHash,
        confidence: 0.95,  // Very high confidence
    })
}

/// Content hash computation (excludes volatile fields)
fn compute_content_hash(issue: &Issue) -> String {
    let mut hasher = Sha256::new();

    // Include: title, description, issue_type, priority, status, external_ref
    // Exclude: id, created_at, updated_at, labels, dependencies, comments

    hasher.update(issue.title.as_bytes());
    hasher.update(issue.description.as_deref().unwrap_or("").as_bytes());
    hasher.update(issue.issue_type.to_string().as_bytes());
    hasher.update(issue.priority.to_string().as_bytes());
    hasher.update(issue.status.to_string().as_bytes());
    if let Some(ref ext) = issue.external_ref {
        hasher.update(ext.as_bytes());
    }

    format\!("{:x}", hasher.finalize())
}
```

### Phase 3: ID Match
```rust
/// Check if incoming issue matches by ID
fn phase3_id_match(
    incoming: &Issue,
    storage: &SqliteStorage,
) -> Option<CollisionMatch> {
    if storage.id_exists(&incoming.id)? {
        Some(CollisionMatch {
            phase: 3,
            existing_id: incoming.id.clone(),
            match_type: MatchType::Id,
            confidence: 1.0,  // Exact match
        })
    } else {
        None
    }
}
```

### Phase 4: No Match (New Issue)
```rust
/// No collision - issue is new
fn phase4_no_match(incoming: &Issue) -> CollisionResult {
    CollisionResult::NewIssue
}
```

### Full Algorithm
```rust
pub fn detect_collision(
    incoming: &Issue,
    storage: &SqliteStorage,
) -> Result<CollisionResult> {
    // Normalize incoming issue first
    let normalized = normalize_issue(incoming)?;

    // Phase 1: External reference match
    if let Some(m) = phase1_external_ref_match(&normalized, storage) {
        return Ok(CollisionResult::Match(m));
    }

    // Phase 2: Content hash match (deduplication)
    if let Some(m) = phase2_content_hash_match(&normalized, storage) {
        return Ok(CollisionResult::Match(m));
    }

    // Phase 3: ID match
    if let Some(m) = phase3_id_match(&normalized, storage) {
        return Ok(CollisionResult::Match(m));
    }

    // Phase 4: No match - new issue
    Ok(phase4_no_match(&normalized))
}
```

### Issue Normalization (Pre-Processing)
```rust
/// Normalize issue before collision detection
fn normalize_issue(issue: &Issue) -> Result<Issue> {
    let mut normalized = issue.clone();

    // Trim whitespace from text fields
    normalized.title = normalized.title.trim().to_string();
    normalized.description = normalized.description.map(|d| d.trim().to_string());

    // Normalize status to lowercase
    normalized.status = normalized.status.to_lowercase().parse()?;

    // Normalize issue type to lowercase
    normalized.issue_type = normalized.issue_type.to_lowercase().parse()?;

    // Validate priority range (0-4)
    normalized.priority = normalized.priority.clamp(0, 4);

    Ok(normalized)
}
```

## Collision Handling Actions
```rust
pub enum CollisionAction {
    /// Update existing issue with incoming data (if newer)
    Update { existing_id: String, incoming: Issue },

    /// Skip import (existing is newer or identical)
    Skip { existing_id: String, reason: String },

    /// Insert as new issue
    Insert { issue: Issue },

    /// Merge fields from both versions
    Merge { existing_id: String, incoming: Issue, strategy: MergeStrategy },
}

fn determine_action(collision: CollisionResult, incoming: &Issue, storage: &SqliteStorage) -> Result<CollisionAction> {
    match collision {
        CollisionResult::NewIssue => {
            Ok(CollisionAction::Insert { issue: incoming.clone() })
        }
        CollisionResult::Match(m) => {
            let existing = storage.get_issue(&m.existing_id)?
                .ok_or(BeadsError::IssueNotFound(m.existing_id.clone()))?;

            // Last-write-wins: compare updated_at
            if incoming.updated_at > existing.updated_at {
                Ok(CollisionAction::Update { 
                    existing_id: m.existing_id, 
                    incoming: incoming.clone() 
                })
            } else {
                Ok(CollisionAction::Skip { 
                    existing_id: m.existing_id, 
                    reason: "Existing is newer".into() 
                })
            }
        }
    }
}
```

